# Day 4 - Salesforce Flow Builder

## 1. What is Flow Builder?

Flow Builder is a Salesforce automation tool used to automate business processes without writing code.

It allows users to:

- Create workflows visually
- Update records automatically
- Make decisions using conditions
- Send notifications and emails
- Reduce manual work

Flow Builder improves productivity and reduces human errors.

---

## 2. Types of Flows

### Screen Flow

A Screen Flow displays screens and collects user input.

Examples:

- Student registration form
- Fee payment form
- Complaint submission form

Characteristics:

- Requires user interaction
- Shows forms/screens
- Runs manually

---

### Record Triggered Flow

A Record Triggered Flow automatically executes when a record is created, updated, or deleted.

Examples:

- Send email after registration
- Update course seats automatically
- Notify faculty when a course becomes full

Characteristics:

- Runs automatically
- No user interaction needed
- Triggered by record changes

